The containment procedures here do a reasonable job of preparing us for the scip, but damn, maybe at least terminate the personnel before incinerating them.

+crit

-crit


Honestly, after the first paragraph of description, I was expecting to hate this. Note that we never received an answer to the natural question,  in the log intact, the description actually misleads us about what is known about the entity. Two, purely in terms of containment breach risk, this thing is Keter and its current containment procedures are woefully inadequate. It can't conceivably be reliably contained without isolating it from the ocean. Granted, that might mean research into how to isolate and contain the scip is ongoing, but the containment procedures should clarify that.

Let me add a third. The submarine log really didn't work for me. It was easy to lose track of who was doing what, and the characters' behavior was pure archetype; the executive's desire to obtain a sample, using an inadequate vessel, after having confirmed the location of the lost shipment, breaks immersion. 










